					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This inscription seems to record a decision of the <hi rend="italic">Sabhā</hi> of Tiraimūr, the <hi rend="italic">Nagarattār</hi> of Tiruviḍaimarudil and some other dignitaries, who had met in the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭakaśālai</hi> of the temple, to set apart the income from a certain (temple) land for the purchase of 180 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of oil required for burning lamps in the temple on the three festival days every month <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi> days of Ārdrā and Śatabhishaj and on Amāvāsyā. Reference is made to the administration (<hi rend="italic">ārāychchi</hi>) of one Vāsudēvanār of Kurumbil.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
